6 4217   Kent. That from your first of difference and decay
6 4218      Have followed your sad steps.
6 4219   Lear. You're welcome hither.
6 4220   Kent. Nor no man else! All's cheerless, dark, and deadly.
6 4221      Your eldest daughters have fordone themselves,
6 4222      And desperately are dead.
6 4223   Lear. Ay, so I think.
6 4224   Alb. He knows not what he says; and vain is it
6 4225      That we present us to him.
