6 4227 
6 4228                            Enter a Captain. 
6 4229 
6 4230   Capt. Edmund is dead, my lord.
6 4231   Alb. That's but a trifle here.
6 4232      You lords and noble friends, know our intent.
6 4233      What comfort to this great decay may come
6 4234      Shall be applied. For us, we will resign,
6 4235      During the life of this old Majesty,
6 4236      To him our absolute power; [to Edgar and Kent] you to your
6 4237         rights;
6 4238      With boot, and Such addition as your honours
6 4239      Have more than merited.- All friends shall taste
6 4240      The wages of their virtue, and all foes
6 4241      The cup of their deservings.- O, see, see!
6 4242   Lear. And my poor fool is hang'd! No, no, no life!
6 4243      Why should a dog, a horse, a rat, have life,
6 4244      And thou no breath at all? Thou'lt come no more,
6 4245      Never, never, never, never, never!
